No data, just maps

BGB =list(lat=52.51628, lon =13.37770) # getGeoCode("Brandenburg Gate, Berlin")
par(pty="s")
#we can be explicit about lat/lon:
mapBG1 = plotmap(BGB$lat, BGB$lon, zoom = 15)

#or we can just pass the named vector:
mapBG2 = plotmap(BGB, zoom = 16, maptype="satellite")

Show traffic on bing maps

BGB =c(lat=52.51628, lon =13.37770) # getGeoCode("Brandenburg Gate, Berlin")
par(pty="s")

mapBG3 = GetBingMap(center=BGB, zoom=12, extraURL="&mapLayer=TrafficFlow", 
                      apiKey=apiKey,verbose=0, destfile="BerlinTraffic.png")
PlotOnStaticMap(mapBG3)

Plots with spatial data

data(incidents)
col=as.numeric(incidents$Category)
par(pty="s", mfrow=c(1,2))

mapSF_Z15 = plotmap(lat, lon, zoom = 15, col = col, pch=20, data = incidents)
#mapSF_Z13 = with(incidents, plotmap(lat, lon, zoom = 13, col = "Category", pch=20))


SundayCrimes = subset(incidents, DayOfWeek=="Sunday")
col=as.numeric(SundayCrimes$violent)
plotmap(lat, lon, zoom = 13, col = col, pch=20, data = SundayCrimes, alpha = 0.5)

OpenStreetMaps

par(pty="s")
lat = c(40.702147,40.718217,40.711614);
  lon = c(-74.012318,-74.015794,-73.998284);
  center = c(mean(lat), mean(lon));
  zoom <- min(MaxZoom(range(lat), range(lon)));
  bb=qbbox(lat,lon)
  
  manhattan_osm = GetMapTiles(latR =bb$latR , lonR=bb$lonR,zoom=zoom,verbose=0)
  PlotOnMapTiles(manhattan_osm,lat=lat,lon=lon,pch=20,col=c('red', 'blue', 'green'),cex=2)

Stamen

par(pty="s", mfrow=c(1,2))

#OSM, Ireland
  xlim = c(-7.5, -2.5) 
  ylim = c(51.35, 55.35)
ir.stamenToner <- GetMapTiles(lonR=xlim, latR=ylim, zoom=7,verbose=0,
                                type = "stamen", tileDir= TRUE)
  PlotOnMapTiles(ir.stamenToner)
  
  
  ir.stamenWater <- GetMapTiles(lonR=xlim, latR=ylim, zoom=7, verbose=0,
                                type = "stamen-watercolor", tileDir= TRUE)
  PlotOnMapTiles(ir.stamenWater)

Conditional Plotting

Using the loa library and a larger crime dataset:

suppressWarnings(require(loa, quietly = TRUE))
suppressWarnings(require(latticeExtra, quietly = TRUE))

data(incidents)

cols <- c("yellow", "darkred")
GoogleMap(~lat*lon|DayOfWeek,         #plot conditioned         
          data=incidents, map=NULL,
          groups=incidents$violent,                                               
          col=cols, cex=0.1, alpha=0.3,                 
          panel=panel.loaPlot2,                         
          key.groups=list(main="Violent", 
                          cex=1, col=cols))    

loa_mapSF <- getMapArg()

Heat Maps:

v <- ifelse(incidents$violent==TRUE, "Violent", "Non-violent")
#weekend versus weekday:
WE = ifelse(incidents$DayOfWeek %in% c("Saturday", "Sunday"),"weekend", "weekday")

useOuterStrips(GoogleMap(~lat*lon|WE+v,         #plot conditioned         
          data=incidents, map=loa_mapSF,
          panel=panel.kernelDensity,                          #surface plot control                                                                
          col.regions=c("lightyellow", "darkred"),            #
          alpha.regions=0.5,                                  #                       
          col=1,                                              #surface calculation    
          n=200, at=c(0.5,1,2.5,5,10,25,50), 
          scales=list(draw=FALSE), xlab="", ylab=""))     
#useOuterStrips(trellis.last.object())
